%1s Feels Time Is Up At %2s

If he's not going to get a chance at %2s, then %1s is prepared to try elsewhere.\n"I realise that there are a lot of talented players at the club, and I'm not that high up the pecking order. But unless I get a fair crack of the whip, I'm going to have to contemplate a future away from the club; as hard as that is to take for me".

%3s have one happy camper in %1s. The %4s is very content with his playing time at the club and says he can't comprehend life elsewhere.\n"Yes it's true that I'm enjoying my football at %3s and have a good relationship with %2s. She seems to value having me in her team and I will do my best to try to repay that trust with some great performances to help the team" he mused.
Lack Of Action Frustrates %1s

%2s doesn't seem to have %1s in his plans this season.\nThe %3s has spent most of recent times kicking his heels and watching the first team play from up in the stands; and he's disappointed.\n"It's no secret that I'd like to play more, and the manager knows that" he said. "I'm not the type of player who can give ultimatums, but I will have to consider my future unless I get more of a chance in the team".

%2s doesn't seem to have %1s in his plans this season.\nThe %3s has spent most of recent times kicking his heels and watching the first team play from up in the stands; and he's disappointed.\n"It's no secret that I'd like to play more, and the manager knows that" he said. "I'm not the type of player who can give ultimatums, but I will have to consider my future unless I get more of a chance in the team".
%1s Ponders %2s Future

Although not one of the first names that you'd expect to find on the teamsheet at %2s, %1s is nevertheless still a frustrated man. "I'm not saying that I should play every game" said the %3s. "But for the sake of my career I need to get more involved in the squad rotation, or I need to look elsewhere to get some first team action" he concluded.\nIt's too early to say if this is the beginning of the end for %1s at %2s, but he is clearly not happy with his current status at the club.

The life of a footballer is not always a happy one, but %1s is certainly content at %3s.\nFollowing the match against %4s, he spoke of how happy he is to play under %2s.\n"The boss and I have a good relationship, I like the way she manages the club" he said. "It's good to be selected for the first team, and I value her as a manager. I hope that I can be successful and help the club achieve great things".
%1s Fuming At Role

Time on the sidelines is not amusing %1s as the out of favour %2s man is clearly fed up with life on the sidelines.\n"I just want to play football and I'm not getting much of a chance" he said during an interview. "I can't say too much really, but I love the club and the fans and it breaks my heart that I'm not being selected for the team" he continued.\n"I've spoken to the boss about it, so it's totally up to him now. I know I can do a job for %2s, so I just want that chance".

Is %1s Part Of %2s Future?

A man not currently enjoying his football is %3s's %1s.\nA player who normally would feel as if he should be one of the first names on the team sheet, has been virtually frozen out of %2s's plans in recent times. Rumours suggest that the %4s looked for showdown talks with the manager, but only in time will we see if these alleged talks will get him back into first team favour, or accelerate his departure from the club.
